LiFi Service (Light‑ Fidelity) is a wireless communication technology that uses visible light, infrared, or ultraviolet light to transmit data. Unlike Wi‑Fi, which relies on radio waves, LiFi employs light‑emitting diodes (LEDs) or other light sources to deliver high‑speed data communication. It is considered a promising alternative to conventional wireless technologies, especially in RF‑restricted zones such as hospitals, aircraft cabins, petrochemical plants, and clean‑room environments.
