What is LiFi Service?
LiFi Service leverages the rapid modulation of light intensity-often at rates imperceptible to the human eye-to encode binary data. A typical LiFi link consists of a transmitter (often integrated into an LED lighting fixture) and a photodetector or camera‑based receiver. Because light does not penetrate opaque barriers, LiFi inherently offers a high level of physical security and is immune to electromagnetic interference, making it attractive for data‑sensitive applications.
